---
description: Tailwind configuration and RTL/dark-mode usage standards
globs: ["front/tailwind.config.js", "front/src/index.css", "front/src/**/*.jsx"]
alwaysApply: true
---

- Tailwind config
  - Keep content globs tight to `./src/**/*.{js,jsx,ts,tsx}`.
  - Extend theme via tokens already provided (colors, fonts, spacing, animations).
  - Use the custom plugin to set `--start/--end` and RTL base rules; do not override in components.

- Dark mode
  - Controlled via `document.documentElement.classList.add('dark')` in `ThemeProvider`.
  - Components should consume `isDark` from theme context if behavioral differences are needed; avoid querying DOM directly.

- Utilities
  - Reuse provided utilities: `.scrollbar-hide`, `.arabic-card`, `.arabic-button`, `.arabic-input`, `.glass-effect`, `.scan-frame`.
  - For new animations, add keyframes in Tailwind config and reference via `animate-*`.

These rules centralize theming and keep RTL behavior consistent.

